cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving machine translation performance using a pre-training method called multilingual denoising. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also involves training a sequence-to-sequence model, which falls under the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses large-scale corpora, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) depending on the type of data used.
